Number = {{1}},
Pages = {{234-245}},
Month = {{JAN}},
Abstract = {{The default mode network (DMN) has been implicated in an array of
   social-cognitive functions, including self-referential processing,
   theory of mind, and mentalizing. Yet, the properties of the external
   stimuli that elicit DMN activity in relation to these domains remain
   unknown. Previous studies suggested that motion kinematics is utilized
